OL,3,CHospice forced to reduce beds and cut
OL,4,C45 full-time roles amid funding crisis
OL,6,F"There is a growing need for
OL,7,Fpalliative and end of life care and
OL,8,Fthe NHS is unable to meet the huge
OL,9,Fdemands on its beds. Most people do
OL,10,Fnot want to die in hospital and
OL,11,Fhospices provide outstanding services
OL,12,Fthat support people to die in a place
OL,13,Fof their choosing."
